item.text: Did you discuss this client's scores with a supervisor?
Please discuss with a supervisor before proceeding

• If the client screened positive for probable suicide risk, determine with the supervisor whether the client should receive Safety Planning Intervention (SPI). By this point, you may have already completed the SPI intervention with the client. Please select "Safety Planning Intervention (SPI)" even if you have already completed it.
  • If the client screened positive for probable common mental health problem, determine with the supervisor whether the client should receive Interpersonal Counseling (IPC).
  • If the client screened positive for probable alcohol use problem and/or drug use problem, determine with the supervisor whether the client should receive SBIRT - Motivational Interviewing.
  • If the client screened positive for probable severe mental health problem, determine with the supervisor whether the client should receive a referral to a mental health specialist. By this point, you may have already documented the client's referral to a mental health specialist. Please select "Referral to mental health specialist" even if you have already completed this.
  • If the client screened positive for any financial hardship, determine with the supervisor whether the client should receive Financial Wellness Supports.

Tip
A safety plan is a personalized emergency plan that clearly describes the clients' warning signs, coping strategies, and resources they use before or during a suicidal crisis. The goal of this intervention is to prevent suicide.

Example dialogue
"Based on what you have shared with me, it sounds like you could benefit from creating a plan that will help keep you safe. If we put our heads together, we can create a plan to help you to stay safe if youre feeling low or have a crisis. Its called a Safety Plan.The Safety Plan is a way to help you better understand what brings about warning signs and create a plan to help prevent a crisis and to take action to reduce risk. Is this something you would be interested in doing?"

Planning Next Steps
Probable common mental health problem

Tip
Interpersonal Counseling (IPC) is a 4-session talk-therapy used to help people deal with current interpersonal problems and come up with solutions to address them. IPC focuses on the 'here' and 'now'.

Example dialogue
"Interpersonal counseling (IPC) can help you find options for improving your situation and come up with ways to deal with your distress, depression, or anxiety. Interpersonal counseling lasts for four sessions. Would you like to start working together on the problems that are contributing to your distress?"
If the client declined, please indicate the reason(s):

Tip
SBIRT (which stands for Screening, Brief Intervention and Referral to Treatment) is a brief intervention which can be offered to people who are experiencing, or are at risk of experiencing, substance use problems. SBIRT provides the client with information about the connection between their health and substance use, while also helping them prevent or reduce substance misuse.

Example dialogue
"SBIRT is a one-session intervention that has been shown to help people reduce their drinking/drug use and achieve their goals. During this session, we can explore how drinking/drug use is impacting different areas of your life, work on identifying any changes you would like to make, and come up with strategies to help you reduce your drinking/drug use. Does this sound like something you would be interested in doing?"
If the client declined, please indicate the reason(s):

Next steps for the client must be discussed with supervisor before proceeding.

Tip #1
The Financial Wellness Tool helps to identify financial stressors and areas of need for the client. Once priority areas have been identified, let the client know there are supports available and provide them with information about the different resources available.

Tip #2
Remind the client that financial services can help them navigate the stressors they are experiencing (i.e., housing, food, cash flow, etc.), and develop achievable financial goals. These services are free and confidential, regardless of immigration status.

Example dialogue
"It sounds like youre facing some financial difficulties. This is very common, and it can be very distressing. To help with this, ENGAGE can offer you Financial Wellness Supports (FWS) and work with you to think about which aspects of your financial situation you would like to work on the most, set concrete goals, and plan specific actions you can take. Your plan will include identifying and connecting you with community resources or other supports that could help you. For example, we may connect you with free financial counseling, employment supports, housing services, and other supports in the community. We will also offer you ongoing support to help you with any barriers you may have in achieving your financial wellness goals. What do you think about this idea?"
Did the client accept Financial Wellness Supports?
If the client declined, please indicate the reason(s):
